time required: 45 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Pre-heat your oven to 220 degrees. Peel and chop your @swede{1} in half, then chop into chip shaped pieces roughly the length of your index finger and 1cm wide. Grate your @parmesan cheese{2}, pull your @rosemary{3} leaves off their stalks and roughly chop them.

Add your swede chips to a #baking tray{}, drizzle over @oil{2%tbsp} and sprinkle over @salt{1/4%tsp}, a good grind of @pepper{} and half your rosemary. Give the tray a good shake and then put in the oven on the top shelf to cook for ~{20%minutes}. When ~{20%minutes} is up, take your swede tray out of the oven, turn the swede chips over, add your parmesan to the baking tray and give it all a good shake. Pop back into the oven on the top shelf to cook for another ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, you can tackle your sausages...pop your @pork & oregano sausages{2} onto another baking tray, prick them each a couple of times with a sharp #knife{} or #fork{} and put them in the oven on the second shelf to cook for ~{30%minutes}, turning halfway through.

In the meantime, you can prepare your veggies and make your red onion relish. Chop your @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice thinly into half moon shapes. Peel and finely chop your @garlic clove{1} and cut your @tenderstem broccoli{1} in half widthways.

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} on low heat in a non-stick #saucepan{}. Add in the red onion slices with @?sugar{1/2%tsp} (if you have some) and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook slowly for ~{10%minutes}, stirring occasionally and then add your @balsamic vinegar{1} and continue cooking slowly for another ~{10-15%minutes}. When the onions are looking lovely and caramelised, put a lid on the pan and leave to the side until everything else is ready.

Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} and once boiling, add your broccoli, boil for ~{3%minutes} before draining and submerging in cold water. About ~{5%minutes} before everything is ready, add @oil{1%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add your broccoli and the rest of your chopped rosemary. Cook for ~{2%minutes} before adding the garlic and stir-frying for a further ~{1%minute}.

Serve your sausages with your swede chips, stir-fried broccoli and your red onion relish on the side. Enjoy!